\subsection{Sync vs Async}{

The \code{async} parameter controls execution mode for all API methods:
\itemize{
\item \code{async = FALSE} (default): methods return results directly (\code{data.table}, character, etc.).
\item \code{async = TRUE}: methods return \link[promises:promise]{promises::promise} objects that resolve to the same types.
}

When async, use \code{\link[coro:async]{coro::async()}} and \code{await()} or \code{\link[promises:then]{promises::then()}} to consume results.
The \code{promises} package must be installed for async mode (\code{Suggests} dependency).
}

\subsection{Timestamp Source}{

The \code{time_source} parameter controls which clock is used for HMAC request
signing:
\itemize{
\item \code{"local"} (default): uses \code{lubridate::now()} from the local machine.
\item \code{"server"}: fetches the KuCoin server time via \code{GET /api/v1/timestamp}
before each authenticated request. This is slower (one extra HTTP round
trip) but ensures signing works even when the local clock is out of sync.
}
}

